== Events == * (【[318]】 _月_日) – The governor of the southern Yangtze region, {{ill|Sima Mo|ja|司馬寞|12=draft|12=draft}}, ascended to the throne proclaiming himself 【元帝】, and the {{ill|Eastern Jin|ja|東晋|12=draft|12=draft}} was established. * {{ill|Eireki|ja|永暦|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1160]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Following defeat in the {{ill|Heiji Rebellion|ja|平治の乱|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|ja|源頼朝|12=draft|12=draft}} was exiled to {{ill|Izu Province|ja|伊豆|12=draft|12=draft}}. * ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1192]] {{ill|April 24|ja|4月24日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In the outskirts of the Southern Song capital, the {{ill|Lugou Bridge|ja|盧溝橋|12=draft|12=draft}} (also known as Marco Polo Bridge) was constructed. * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1582]] {{ill|April 3|ja|4月3日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – After the combined forces of {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|ja|信長|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|家康|12=draft|12=draft}} defeated him, {{ill|Takeda Katsuyori|ja|武田勝頼|12=draft|12=draft}} committed suicide, leading to the downfall of the {{ill|Takeda clan|ja|武田氏|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|12=draft|12=draft}} 13rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1608]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Having resigned as Commander-in-Chief, {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康|12=draft|12=draft}} relocated to {{ill|Sunpu Castle|ja|駿府城|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Births == * {{ill|Kansei|ja|寛政|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1800]] {{ill|April 4|ja|4月4日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Saira|ja|徳川斉昭|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 9th head of the {{ill|Mito Domain|ja|水戸藩主|12=draft|12=draft}} and father of {{ill|Tokugawa Yoshinobu|ja|徳川慶喜|12=draft|12=draft}} (died [[1860]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1834]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hashimoto Sanao|ja|橋本左内|12=draft|12=draft}}, a samurai of the {{ill|Fukui Domain|ja|福井藩|12=draft|12=draft}} (died [[1859]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Shinmu Tennō|ja|神武天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} 76th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[585 BC]] {{ill|April 9|ja|4月9日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shinmu Tennō|ja|神武天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, the first {{ill|Emperor of Japan|ja|天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} (born [[585 BC]] or another traditional date). * ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[618]] {{ill|April 11|ja|4月11日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Yang Emperor|ja|煬帝|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 2nd emperor of the {{ill|Sui Dynasty|ja|隋|12=draft|12=draft}} (born [[569]]). * {{ill|Ōan|ja|応安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year/{{ill|Shōhei|ja|正平|12=draft|12=draft}} 23rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1368]] {{ill|March 29|ja|3月29日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Go-Murakami Tennō|ja|後村上天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 97th emperor (born [[1328]]). * In Tenshō 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1582]] {{ill|April 3|ja|4月3日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Takeda Katsuyori|ja|武田勝頼|12=draft|12=draft}}, a samurai and son of {{ill|Takeda Shingen|ja|武田信玄|12=draft|12=draft}} (born [[1546]]).
