{{Not to be confused with|March 11|qq=March 11}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月十一|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 11일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 11''' is the 11th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜}}.
== Events == * (【[318]】 _月_日) – The governor of the southern Yangtze region, {{ill|Sima Mo|ja|司馬寞|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sima Mo|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, ascended to the throne proclaiming himself 【元帝】, and the {{ill|Eastern Jin|ja|東晋|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eastern Jin|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} was established. * [[:en:Eiryaku|Eireki]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1160|1160]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – Following defeat in the [[:en:Heiji rebellion|Heiji Rebellion]], [[:en:Minamoto no Yoritomo|Minamoto no Yoritomo]] was exiled to {{ill|Izu Province|ja|伊豆|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izu Province|qq=}}. * ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1192|1192]] [[:en:April 24|April 24]]) – In the outskirts of the Southern Song capital, the [[:en:Marco Polo Bridge|Lugou Bridge]] (also known as Marco Polo Bridge) was constructed. * [[:en:Tenshō (Momoyama period)|Tenshō Era]] 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1582]] [[:en:April 3|April 3]]) – After the combined forces of {{ill|Oda Nobunaga|ja|信長|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oda Nobunaga|qq=}} and {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|家康|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa Ieyasu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 徳川家康}} defeated him, [[:en:Takeda Katsuyori|Takeda Katsuyori]] committed suicide, leading to the downfall of the [[:en:Takeda clan|Takeda clan]]. * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 13rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1608]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – Having resigned as Commander-in-Chief, [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]] relocated to [[:en:Sunpu Castle|Sunpu Castle]].
== Births == * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1800]] [[:en:April 4|April 4]]) – [[:en:Tokugawa Nariaki|Tokugawa Saira]], the 9th head of the [[:en:Mito Domain|Mito Domain]] and father of [[:en:Tokugawa Yoshinobu|Tokugawa Yoshinobu]] (died [[1860]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1834]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – [[:en:Hashimoto Sanai|Hashimoto Sanao]], a samurai of the [[:en:Fukui Domain|Fukui Domain]] (died [[1859]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Emperor Jimmu|Shinmu Tennō]] 76th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[585 BC]] [[:en:April 9|April 9]]) – [[:en:Emperor Jimmu|Shinmu Tennō]], the first [[:en:Emperor of Japan|Emperor of Japan]] (born [[585 BC]] or another traditional date). * ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[618]] [[:en:April 11|April 11]]) – [[:en:Emperor Yang of Sui|Yang Emperor]], the 2nd emperor of the [[:en:Sui dynasty|Sui Dynasty]] (born [[569]]). * [[:en:Ōan|Ōan era]] 1st year/[[:en:Zhengping|Shōhei]] 23rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1368|1368]] [[:en:March 29|March 29]]) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Murakami|Go-Murakami Tennō]], the 97th emperor (born [[:en:1328|1328]]). * In Tenshō 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1582]] [[:en:April 3|April 3]]) – [[:en:Takeda Katsuyori|Takeda Katsuyori]], a samurai and son of [[:en:Takeda Shingen|Takeda Shingen]] (born [[:en:1546|1546]]).
