{{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月十一|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 11일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 11''' is the 11th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshū|qid=Q96759839|1=senshū}}{{efn|ja|先勝|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.
== Events == * (【[318]】 _月_日) – The governor of the southern Yangtze region, {{ill|Sima Mo|ja|司馬寞|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sima Mo|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, ascended to the throne proclaiming himself 【元帝】, and the {{ill|Eastern Jin|ja|東晋|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eastern Jin|comment=changed title based on wikidata|1=Eastern Jin|qid=Q306928}} was established. * {{ill|Eiryaku|en|Eiryaku|qid=Q1193895|lt=Eireki|1=Eiryaku}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1160|en|1160|qid=Q19662|lt=1160|1=1160}} {{ill|April 19|en|April 19|qid=Q2523|lt=April 19|1=April 19}}) – Following defeat in the {{ill|Heiji rebellion|en|Heiji rebellion|qid=Q944859|lt=Heiji Rebellion|1=Heiji rebellion}}, {{ill|Minamoto no Yoritomo|en|Minamoto no Yoritomo|qid=Q242800|lt=Minamoto no Yoritomo|1=Minamoto no Yoritomo}} was exiled to {{ill|Izu (disambiguation)|ja|伊豆|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izu Province|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q16766555|lt=Izu|1=Izu (disambiguation)}}. * ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1192|en|1192|qid=Q19739|lt=1192|1=1192}} {{ill|April 24|en|April 24|qid=Q2529|lt=April 24|1=April 24}}) – In the outskirts of the Southern Song capital, the {{ill|Marco Polo Bridge|en|Marco Polo Bridge|qid=Q1060121|lt=Lugou Bridge|1=Marco Polo Bridge}} (also known as Marco Polo Bridge) was constructed. * {{ill|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|en|Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qid=Q1145058|lt=Tenshō Era|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1582|en|1582|qid=Q6719|lt=1582|1=1582}} {{ill|April 3|en|April 3|qid=Q2509|lt=April 3|1=April 3}}) – After the combined forces of [[Oda Nobunaga]] and {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|家康|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 徳川家康|1=Tokugawa Ieyasu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q171977}} defeated him, {{ill|Takeda Katsuyori|en|Takeda Katsuyori|qid=Q662482|lt=Takeda Katsuyori|1=Takeda Katsuyori}} committed suicide, leading to the downfall of the {{ill|Takeda clan|en|Takeda clan|qid=Q1210114|lt=Takeda clan|1=Takeda clan}}. * {{ill|Keichō|en|Keichō|qid=Q1328185|lt=Keichō|1=Keichō}} 13rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1608|en|1608|qid=Q6758|lt=1608|1=1608}} {{ill|April 25|en|April 25|qid=Q2531|lt=April 25|1=April 25}}) – Having resigned as Commander-in-Chief, {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|en|Tokugawa Ieyasu|qid=Q171977|lt=Tokugawa Ieyasu|1=Tokugawa Ieyasu}} relocated to {{ill|Sunpu Castle|en|Sunpu Castle|qid=Q1038629|lt=Sunpu Castle|1=Sunpu Castle}}.
== Births == * {{ill|Kansei|en|Kansei|qid=Q1195131|lt=Kansei|1=Kansei}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1800|en|1800|qid=Q6875|lt=1800|1=1800}} {{ill|April 4|en|April 4|qid=Q2508|lt=April 4|1=April 4}}) – {{ill|Tokugawa Nariaki|en|Tokugawa Nariaki|qid=Q1323770|lt=Tokugawa Saira|1=Tokugawa Nariaki}}, the 9th head of the {{ill|Mito Domain|en|Mito Domain|qid=Q1146904|lt=Mito Domain|1=Mito Domain}} and father of {{ill|Tokugawa Yoshinobu|en|Tokugawa Yoshinobu|qid=Q287657|lt=Tokugawa Yoshinobu|1=Tokugawa Yoshinobu}} (died {{ill|1860|en|1860|qid=Q7691|lt=1860|1=1860}}). * {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1834|en|1834|qid=Q7591|lt=1834|1=1834}} {{ill|April 19|en|April 19|qid=Q2523|lt=April 19|1=April 19}}) – {{ill|Hashimoto Sanai|en|Hashimoto Sanai|qid=Q1036286|lt=Hashimoto Sanao|1=Hashimoto Sanai}}, a samurai of the {{ill|Fukui Domain|en|Fukui Domain|qid=Q903537|lt=Fukui Domain|1=Fukui Domain}} (died {{ill|1859|en|1859|qid=Q7687|lt=1859|1=1859}}).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Emperor Jimmu|en|Emperor Jimmu|qid=Q200188|lt=Shinmu Tennō|1=Emperor Jimmu}} 76th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|585 BC|en|585 BC|qid=Q1059158|lt=585 BC|1=585 BC}} {{ill|April 9|en|April 9|qid=Q2504|lt=April 9|1=April 9}}) – {{ill|Emperor Jimmu|en|Emperor Jimmu|qid=Q200188|lt=Shinmu Tennō|1=Emperor Jimmu}}, the first {{ill|Emperor of Japan|en|Emperor of Japan|qid=Q208233|lt=Emperor of Japan|1=Emperor of Japan}} (born {{ill|585 BC|en|585 BC|qid=Q1059158|lt=585 BC|1=585 BC}} or another traditional date). * ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|618|en|618|qid=Q31035|lt=618|1=618}} {{ill|April 11|en|April 11|qid=Q2501|lt=April 11|1=April 11}}) – {{ill|Emperor Yang of Sui|en|Emperor Yang of Sui|qid=Q7419|lt=Yang Emperor|1=Emperor Yang of Sui}}, the 2nd emperor of the {{ill|Sui dynasty|en|Sui dynasty|qid=Q7405|lt=Sui Dynasty|1=Sui dynasty}} (born {{ill|569|en|569|qid=Q33409|lt=569|1=569}}). * {{ill|Ōan|en|Ōan|qid=Q1146245|lt=Ōan era|1=Ōan}} 1st year/{{ill|Zhengping|en|Zhengping|qid=Q11123413|lt=Shōhei|1=Zhengping}} 23rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1368|en|1368|qid=Q6207|lt=1368|1=1368}} {{ill|March 29|en|March 29|qid=Q2459|lt=March 29|1=March 29}}) – {{ill|Emperor Go-Murakami|en|Emperor Go-Murakami|qid=Q440447|lt=Go-Murakami Tennō|1=Emperor Go-Murakami}}, the 97th emperor (born {{ill|1328|en|1328|qid=Q5802|lt=1328|1=1328}}). * In Tenshō 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1582|en|1582|qid=Q6719|lt=1582|1=1582}} {{ill|April 3|en|April 3|qid=Q2509|lt=April 3|1=April 3}}) – {{ill|Takeda Katsuyori|en|Takeda Katsuyori|qid=Q662482|lt=Takeda Katsuyori|1=Takeda Katsuyori}}, a samurai and son of {{ill|Takeda Shingen|en|Takeda Shingen|qid=Q276404|lt=Takeda Shingen|1=Takeda Shingen}} (born {{ill|1546|en|1546|qid=Q6533|lt=1546|1=1546}}).
